docs.lead_paragraph: The dollar registered a sharp advance in terms of the foreign currencies last week. Measured by the quotation for the French franc of 6.45 cents, on Tuesday, the dollar stood at a premium of 2.8 cents, over the franc parity. This is the highest for the dollar since Feb. 9, 1934.
